WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.980
Chapter 25 of Proverbs, King James Version.

00:04.260 --> 00:09.140
This LibriVox recording is in the public domain, recording by Michael Packard.

00:10.280 --> 00:16.020
These are the Proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah, king of Judah, copied out.

00:16.880 --> 00:23.640
It is the glory of God to conceal a thing, but the honor of kings is to search out a

00:23.640 --> 00:23.960
matter.

00:24.860 --> 00:30.720
The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings, is unsearchable.

00:31.540 --> 00:37.260
Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.

00:37.860 --> 00:43.560
Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.

00:45.620 --> 00:50.760
Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great

00:50.760 --> 00:51.200
men.

00:51.720 --> 00:57.080
For better it is that it be said unto thee, Come up hither, and that thou shouldest be

00:57.080 --> 01:00.960
put lower in the presence of the prince whom thine eyes have seen.

01:01.740 --> 01:08.340
Go not forth hastily to strive, lest thou know not what to do in the end thereof, when

01:08.340 --> 01:10.660
thy neighbor hath put thee to shame.

01:11.560 --> 01:17.960
Debate thy cause with thy neighbor himself, and discover not a secret to another, lest

01:17.960 --> 01:22.340
he that heareth it put thee to shame, and thine infamy turn not away.

01:23.760 --> 01:29.380
A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in pictures of silver.

01:30.080 --> 01:38.480
As an earring of gold in an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient

01:38.480 --> 01:39.060
ear.

01:39.960 --> 01:46.140
As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to them that send

01:46.960 --> 01:49.800
for he refresheth the soul of his masters.

01:50.680 --> 01:57.760
Whoso boasteth himself of a false gift is like clouds and wind without rain.

01:58.540 --> 02:04.540
By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.

02:05.440 --> 02:06.960
Hast thou found honey?

02:07.360 --> 02:12.580
Eat so much as is sufficient for thee, lest thou be filled therewith and vomit it.

02:13.900 --> 02:19.840
Withdraw thy foot from thy neighbor's house, lest he be weary of thee and so hate thee.

02:20.920 --> 02:27.120
A man that beareth false witness against his neighbor is a maul and a sword and a sharp

02:27.120 --> 02:27.720
arrow.

02:28.760 --> 02:34.600
Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth and a foot

02:34.600 --> 02:35.540
out of joint.

02:36.340 --> 02:44.380
As he that taketh away a garment in cold weather, and as vinegar upon nitra, so is he that singeth

02:44.380 --> 02:46.220
songs to an heavy heart.

02:47.940 --> 02:53.920
If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat, and if he be thirsty, give him water

02:53.920 --> 03:00.640
to drink, for thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the Lord shall reward thee.

03:01.060 --> 03:07.020
The north wind driveth away rain, so doth an angry countenance a backbiting tongue.

03:07.740 --> 03:13.800
It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop than with a brawling woman and in

03:13.800 --> 03:15.020
a wide house.

03:17.080 --> 03:23.120
As cold waters to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.

03:24.160 --> 03:31.340
A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a troubled fountain and a corrupt spring.

03:32.300 --> 03:38.000
It is not good to eat much honey, so for men to search their own glory is not glory.

03:38.820 --> 03:45.180
He that hath no rule over his own spirit is like a city that is broken down and without

03:45.180 --> 03:45.980
walls.

